eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu. #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Heavy rains are wreaking havoc in Gauteng with areas around the Vaal river system now being flooded. READ: Heavy rains batter parts of SA Authorities have been forced to open 12 sluice gates as the Vaal Dam has filled to overflowing after exceeding its 100 percent capacity. Several areas have been battered with residents being evacuated. eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu has more details in the video above.